# Development Environment Standards

> **Note**: Assumes core rules (command execution, file operations) are already loaded.

## OS Detection Protocol
Always determine the operating system before executing commands:
```bash
uname -s  # Linux/Darwin/MINGW64_NT (Git Bash on Windows)
echo $OS  # Windows_NT on Windows
```

## Windows PowerShell
- Use `Get-ChildItem` instead of `ls`
- Use `Remove-Item` instead of `rm`
- Use `Copy-Item` instead of `cp`
- Use backslashes `\` for paths
- Use `Test-Path` to check file existence
- Use `choco install` or `winget install` for packages

## Ubuntu/Linux
- Use standard Unix commands: `ls`, `rm`, `cp`, `mv`
- Use `apt` for packages: `sudo apt install package`
- Use forward slashes `/` for paths
- Use `which command` to find executables
- Use `export VAR=value` for environment variables

## Common Development Tools (Cross-Platform)
- Git: `git status`, `git add .`, `git commit -m "message"`
- Node.js: `npm install`, `npm run build`, `npm test`
- Python: `python -m venv venv`, `pip install -r requirements.txt`
- Docker: `docker build -t image-name .`, `docker run -p 8080:8080 image-name`

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- ❌ Using `ls` on Windows PowerShell
- ❌ Using `Get-ChildItem` on Linux
- ❌ Mixing path separators (`/` vs `\`)
- ❌ Running commands without OS detection

## Environment Validation
Check required tools before use:
```bash
git --version
node --version
python --version
docker --version
```
